summary_to_eng: Add coloring of linked user cards
Text_Summa: Add coloring of linked user cards [~takt911] Coloring the linked map is done in such a way; in the appendix there is a list with a color palette of 10 gradients; we sum the last 4 digits of the map and take the remainder of the division by 10; as a result we get a number from 0 to 9; which we substitute into our list with palettes and pull out the gradient. Thus; on different phones under the same account in the application; the same card will be painted with the same color; but unfortunately there may be duplicate colors; but I think that is rare. Do you like this logic of card coloring?[~pavel] Ok; I'll have to test it; users usually don't have many cards; but even then there is a risk that; for example; only 2 cards are tied up and both will be in the same colorcards are displayed in the color that is attached to them. all OK

MIC-301 Social login networks Authorization through Google cannot be done simply through allauth. The user will have to redirect to apihi and the api will have to record the session. You should not do this; because in this case; for some users we will have authorization by tokens without sessions; and for others without tokens; but with sessions. You will need to dig into the doc: [https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/OAuth2WebServer] and integrate it into our token authorization process. Unfortunately there is no obvious documentation in the rest-auth docThen I searched / studied different packages for authorization by social networks. networks; trying to apply a solution that authorized only by tokens; avoiding sessions. I even started to implement an authorization service that absolutely does not save state and does not use sessions; having previously tried to find similar solutions on the Internet - I did not find it. As a result; I quit this case; because I came to the conclusion that the solution is absolutely pointless and I did not find a similar solution in Google for this very reason.

By the business requirements _Terms and Condition_ should be accepted by a user; so as we have the Terms and Condition acceptance step is the last and there could a case when the sign-up process could be terminated by accident. But on the previous steps all filled in data are saved; so further a user without acceptance can already sign-in and use the services at all.[~kairat] the simplest way to solve it is adding one more attribute to a response after sign-in. It would be a boolean attribute; which described have users accept the terms or not. Then the frontend can add a message to users about this state. And disable functions if it's needed.another issue is there is no endpoint of customers to specify which kind of notification to receive - email; sms or both.in docs i cant find the way to specify to accept terms by a customer. if there is the way; so which endpoint is that?sign in endpoint is broken now; it is returning 404for customer there is no way to save addressthere is an issue of signup endpoint; the password field is throwing error - password must be 6 chars even if send "Hello2012".[~kairat] and [~samat.jukeshov] here is the documents for Customer Registration End Points:when trying to sign up with data:customer signup* Updated documentation for Customer Sign up [https://gitlab.com/sortedhouse/backend/blob/feature/SOR-30/docs/api.md#sign-up]

Can't play video in Kelley !Screen Shot 2020-04-24 at 21.07.27.png![~azat17] I see this error when click Play button.I chased for this error locally and in the end the result seemed to be the same as i supposed earlier. The error appears because in preview.js script at the line 46 it gets the url value from href attribute like so var href = $(this).attr('href') and tries to do this replacing action href = href.replace( /d1mjfb268gelin.cloudfront.net/g; "daevt1q1a24kq.cloudfront.net"). This action are being taken on the element with class equal to .lecture-preview. But its content can either have or not have the href attribute based on its asset_type field. When asset_type field's value is other than 'Video' then the .lecture-preview element remain without href element and replacing function is executed on the href attribute which's null.FYI the test staging for Kelley is http://kelley2-staging.edumall.io/[~azat17]: in case lecture does not have video url; we should display an error notification. It'll help user avoid confusing when use.This task is frozen because we are moving Azat to https://jira.topica.vn/browse/ETBA-58[~ducla5]; re-assigned this one to youBecause field asset_type have value is "HTML" when user upload video so that we can't play video. Change value to "Video" will resolve this issue.

Cannot reset my password [~ducla5] Researched reset password functionality. Checked it in staging and prod. There appears an error in both Prod and Staging. After clicking on "Forgot password?" link I was redirected to AccountKit page. Researched AccountKit service. I turns out that AccountKit is the Facebook's service for authentication without using passwords. AccountKit's workflow is as follow it uses emails and phone numbers where it sends codes; after which a user should enter that code and if the code is valid a user gets redirected back to their page where special callback handlers handle the data with user's token. If everything in that workflow is ok the page for changing password is opened and a user will be able to type new password.[~ducla5][~ducla5] we use gmail for sending letters but gmail restricts us to send 500 letter in a day. Actually I would like to have all JS files minified and merged in 2-5 files (or more); but not 100+ like we have now; this is insane. Also I see some js files loading but they are the same.default bundling/merging/minification (+10 points on average)Regarding js optimizarion; I suggest to use builtin functionality. summary_to_eng: IAP research from the development side
Text_Summa: IAP research from the development side I read the current conversation with apple about IAP.Checked SandBox users; removed unknown users.Tested with David IAP:While testing I found the problem with IAP.

IAP payment system implementation The check for validation from apple is sent from the application to the backend; if for some reason the check didn't reach the backend; I think that the user's money will be withdrawn and of course; it's not bought; then we need to check and fix it.Added handlers for recording and storing failed purchases.Added removing on logout stored failed purchases which not validated from the backend.Create the 3.1.3 (1000) staging config build.

Testing payments process implementation I still see problems with IAP 2:Tried to add non-renewable purchase; as it turned out; it is impossible to make purchases with the same bundle identifier; but then we can restore the purchase through the apple.There are 2 solutions to the problem:Tasks by the pointsCreate and sent the 3.1.3 (999) build with staging configuration for testing IAP purchases. Describe info about IAP purchase on staging in the chat.For some unknown reason; Yann and Kirill can't make purchases through IAP; Apple rejected the purchase; added the display of the error text; create a new build to testflight 3.1.3 (1001).We sorted out and fixed problems with IAP purchases.I research the problem with error "Cannot connect to iTunes Store"; which rejected the purchases.There was a question with a choice of type of purchase in apple; consumable/ not consumable.I successfully bought the course from IAP purchases; and now disable buy button until we make sure that everything worked successfully.

Text_Summa: Adjust UI on the Payment Page and Thank you page *Report:**Report:**Report:*[~dsalamau] here are some comments on the payment page*Report:*Link to QA[~dsalamau]*Report:*[~dsalamau]*Report:**Report:*Looks good on production [~dsalamau] [~kirill]

Discount function in online payment We have third party service where this landing gets info from. For base url of this service is the same as this site. For example in production there is a request being made for this url [https://epayment.edumall.co.th/api/courses] to grab courses' info also there're some discount values ​​being returned from this request. I checked Meduza in case if it's that service but it isn't. Also reading the code i found that some part of the payment are being made in that service so i need to know it and look at it's code. In main.js at 200 the line there is a call to complete a payment.[~peerapat] can you please give info about the service from your screenshot ? What's the service and maybe you have a link to the repository? I guess it's the service where the requests mentioned above are being sent toYou can access below link:A few updates. Found that data of courses that the site receives are being taken from meduza. Also figured out that discount amount exists in that data. Also figured out that this [https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] java service gets parameters from lending to complete a payment and that params include Omise token and the rest of the payment process is handled by [e -payment|https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] service. All that we need to do is go send that discount to [e-payment|https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/e-payment] service as an additional parameter and change the amount of the price considering that discount.[~peerapat] should the discount from your screen be directly deducted from the price as a certain value or it's a percentage that should be deducted from the price ? In your screen it's 50. Does it mean that we should deduct 50 from the price ?[~peerapat] we also currently do not have discount information displayed on the page . I think we should display it somewhere; right? If so; can you please suggest where it should be. For example for chinesetoday-english.edumall.co.th it's 50. summary_to_eng: The system did not change the status of some leads from incomplete to timeout
Text_Summa: The system did not change the status of some leads from incomplete to timeout Normally; Lead type "c3_credit" has 4 main e-payment status. (Ideally; it should be like to logic below)Went through Minerva; Marol and e-payment applications. Didn't find any code; especially background jobs (crons) that would handle functionality of changing statuses. Found schedulers in e-payment java service and started to investigate it; it also has requests to Marol. But figured out that requests are for changing Ibanking status. Still need to look for this functionality[~Yann] FYI. A few updates.[~azat17] Please note that this issue occurs only a few percent. Most of the contacts status were changed correctly.Had a call with Saran. Regarding this task as i mentioned before the problem of updating statuses occurs because some Contactc3s have priority equal to 3. Found that js landing ([https://git.edumall.io/edumalltl/etl-epayment-gate]) sends a request to change priority to 3 when Omise returns failure response when a user does payments. I consider that some percent of contactc3 had an error returned from Omise. It can happen when the submitted data is incorrect or outdated (card number; cvv; expiration date) or when there isn't enough money on the cardThank you [~azat17].[~saran] sure; okay[~saran] Actually it was a research ticket. I spent the time investigating how does the system change statuses to timeout and found the reason why some leads have their statuses not changed to timeout due to priority being equal to 3. There is nothing to deploy here[~azat17] Could you give me a bit more detail?[~saran][~azat17] From your third answer (3); if the customer got 3 as their priority; why does it changed to failed?[~saran] You mean why despite having priority equal to 3 it doesn't change status to failed ? Correct me please if i'm wrong[~azat17] Correct.[~saran] let me research it

The user cannot login Invalid email or password.!99_1.png|thumbnail!I can successfully login/logout using my account.[~azat17] can you please take a look from an SSO side.I can reproduce this issue using prod db in local env.Issue related to quote items of this particular user. Since this user complains via phone that he can't login to his account on production; we can clean his quote manually through database as a quick solution.[~denis.petrov] [~kirill]From the code side; there are 2 magento core bugs here:

LMS issues - investigate and fix Here's our assumption at the moment.Checked all sidekiq workers whether they consume too much resources or not. Sidekiq was fine and we didn't notice huge memory consumption by it. We checked unicorn server and its configs. During the timeout we didn't see that unicorn consumes too much memory however it wasn't giving a response so afterwards we decided to increase the number of unicorn workers to 9 and reduced the request timeout speed from 600 sec to 30 sec. It helped now. If this issue happens again we're going to increase the number of unicorn workers and see how it affects the memory and plan our next stepsconfirm.[~ducla5] yeah; right. I hope we find the root. It couldn't have appeared from nothing because it used to be ok in previous weeks
